{"id": "unknown-2026-05-21-009", "date": "2026-05-21", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 5, "week": 21, "weekday": "Thu"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["panel_price", "oled_penetration"], "sentiment": {"label": "positive", "score": 0.5, "keywords": ["growth"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "Omdia: the <5-inch automotive AMOLED market set to grow quickly as car makers look for emotional and differentiated aesthetics", "content": "<p>Omdia shared an interesting forecast, looking at small-sized automotive AMOLED displays (under 5 inches). Omdia estimates that 200,000 displays shipped in 2025, but the market will grow fast and reach 1.5 million units by 2030 (a total growth of 541%).</p><img src=\"https://www.oled-info.com/sites/default/files/inline-images/Automotive-OLED-shipments-2025-2030-Omdia.jpg\" data-entity-uuid=\"4494f42d-12c6-4377-9172-9534861ea793\" data-entity-type=\"file\" width=\"501\" height=\"248\" loading=\"lazy\"><p>O", "sources": [{"name": "oled_info", "url": "https://www.oled-info.com/omdia-under-5-inch-automotive-amoled-market-will-grow-200000-units-2025-to15", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-05-21-010", "date": "2026-05-21", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 5, "week": 21, "weekday": "Thu"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["earnings"], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": []}, "importance": {"score": 0.75, "reasons": ["涉及財報"]}, "title": "xFusion drives CNY58.2 billion revenue as China backs domestic AI supply chain", "content": "Chinese server maker xFusion reached a revenue of CNY58.2 billion (approx. US$8.6 billion) for the year 2025. The figure indicates the company's rising profits as it benefits from China's push for a domestic AI supply chain and the benefits for companies breaking into the country's high-end server market.", "sources": [{"name": "digitimes_display", "url": "https://www.digitimes.com/news/a20260521VL224/huawei-xfusion-revenue-supply-chain-china.html", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-05-21-011", "date": "2026-05-21", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 5, "week": 21, "weekday": "Thu"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["earnings"], "sentiment": {"label": "positive", "score": 0.5, "keywords": ["growth"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.75, "reasons": ["涉及財報"]}, "title": "Anthropic estimates show US$559 million operating profit on US$10.9 billion quarter", "content": "<p class=\"P1\" data-path-to-node=\"15\">Anthropic has unlocked an era of explosive commercial growth, hitting a milestone with its first-ever profitable quarter. According to <em>The Wall Street Journal</em>, Anthropic expects its revenue to surge by 130% to hit US$10.9 billion for the quarter ending in June, up from the US$4.8 billion in revenue generated during the first quarter of 2026. This trajectory is projected to yield an inaugural quarterly operating profit of approximately US$559 million.", "sources": [{"name": "digitimes_display", "url": "https://www.digitimes.com/news/a20260521VL219/anthropic-ai-operating-profit-revenue-growth.html", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-05-21-012", "date": "2026-05-21", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 5, "week": 21, "weekday": "Thu"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["earnings"], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": []}, "importance": {"score": 0.75, "reasons": ["涉及財報"]}, "title": "How Nvidia plans to sell Vera CPUs: Four deployment models explained", "content": "Nvidia has unveiled a strategic expansion of its silicon portfolio, detailing a four-pronged commercial approach for its new Vera central processing unit. The chipmaker expects the processor to generate US$20 billion in standalone revenue, signaling a significant evolution in its hardware distribution strategy and a broader play for infrastructure dominance in the emerging agentic artificial intelligence market.", "sources": [{"name": "digitimes_display", "url": "https://www.digitimes.com/news/a20260521VL220/nvidia-silicon-sales-expansion-processor.html", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-05-21-013", "date": "2026-05-21", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 5, "week": 21, "weekday": "Thu"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["earnings"], "sentiment": {"label": "positive", "score": 0.5, "keywords": ["expand"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.75, "reasons": ["涉及財報"]}, "title": "Nvidia targets long-term ACIE dominance as enterprise AI eclipses hyperscalers", "content": "Nvidia has detailed a significant structural shift in its data center revenue reporting, introducing a new market segmentation that separates traditional hyperscale cloud providers from a rapidly expanding sector named ACIE, which stands for artificial intelligence clouds, industrial, and enterprise. While hyperscale platforms currently lead initial deployment, management projects that the ACIE segment will eventually outgrow them, owing to the massive scale of the global corporate economy.", "sources": [{"name": "digitimes_display", "url": "https://www.digitimes.com/news/a20260521VL221/nvidia-industrial-data-center-market-revenue.html", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-05-21-014", "date": "2026-05-21", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 5, "week": 21, "weekday": "Thu"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["earnings"], "sentiment": {"label": "positive", "score": 0.5, "keywords": ["growth"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.75, "reasons": ["涉及財報"]}, "title": "GigaDevice sees niche DRAM and NAND prices rising through 2026", "content": "GigaDevice said tight supply and rising prices across DRAM, NOR Flash, and SLC NAND Flash continued to fuel strong first-quarter 2026 earnings growth, supported by recovering demand from AI, server, and industrial applications.", "sources": [{"name": "digitimes_display", "url": "https://www.digitimes.com/news/a20260521VL208/gigadevice-dram-nand-2026-niche.html?chid=10", "type": "rss"}]}
